The paper discusses security issues in Software-Defined Networking (SDN) infrastructure, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of Intel Software Guard Extensions (SGX) for secure deployment of SDN components and protection of communication between network endpoints suggests the paper may also belong to the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
